fields.name: Last assessment score
fields.formula: join(filter(concat(lookup('Supplier assessments','Result'),' (',lookup('Supplier assessments','Score'),')'),lookup('Supplier assessments','Date') = field('Last assessment date')),'')

fields.name: Active Products & Services
fields.formula: filter(lookup('Contracts','Product or service'),or(lookup('Contracts','Status') = '🟢 Active',lookup('Contracts','Status') = '🟡 Expires in 30 days'))

fields.name: Count active Products & Services 2
fields.formula: count(filter(lookup('Contracts','Product or service'),or(lookup('Contracts','Status') = '🟢 Active',lookup('Contracts','Status') = '🟡 Expires in 30 days')))

fields.name: Total in orders
fields.formula: field('Currently shipped') + field('Currently approved') + field('Currently requested')

fields.name: Below minimum (inc.)
fields.formula: field('Current + in order stock')- field('Minimum stock') < 0

fields.name: Active supplier id
fields.formula: min(filter(lookup('Contracts','Supplier ID'),or(lookup('Contracts','Status') = '🟢 Active',lookup('Contracts','Status') = '🟡 Expires in 30 days')))

rows.field_50514: A contract where the supplier delivers goods or services for a set total price, regardless of actual costs incurred.
A contract where the supplier is reimbursed for actual costs plus an additional fee or profit margin.
A contract where payment is based on the actual time spent and materials used, suitable for tasks with uncertain scope.
A long-term agreement setting terms and conditions for future purchases, but without guaranteeing volume.
A contract defining expected service standards, performance metrics, and penalties for non-compliance.
A contract where the organization rents or leases assets (e.g., equipment, vehicles) instead of purchasing them outright.
A recurring payment contract for ongoing access to a product or service, often software, cloud, or utilities.
A flexible contract used when exact quantities or delivery times are not known at the start.
A contract granting a supplier the right to operate and profit from a service while meeting agreed obligations.
A contract covering ongoing upkeep, repairs, or support for equipment, systems, or facilities.
